content.text:
Found it! The project has **shadcn/ui form components** with react-hook-form integration:

## Available Form Components (`shared/components/ui/`)

| Component | File | Purpose |
|-----------|------|---------|
| `Form`, `FormField`, `FormItem`, `FormLabel`, `FormControl`, `FormMessage` | `form.tsx` | react-hook-form integration |
| `Input` | `input.tsx` | Styled input (`h-12`, `border-2`, `rounded-md`) |
| `Select`, `SelectTrigger`, `SelectContent`, `SelectItem` | `select.tsx` | Radix Select with styling |
| `Button` | `button.tsx` | CVA variants (default, secondary, outline, etc.) |
| `Checkbox` | `checkbox.tsx` | Radix Checkbox |
| `Textarea` | `textarea.tsx` | Styled textarea |

## Proper Form Pattern

```tsx
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod";
import { Form, FormField, FormItem, FormLabel, FormControl, FormMessage } from "@/shared/components/ui/form";
import { Input } from "@/shared/components/ui/input";
import { Select, SelectTrigger, SelectValue, SelectContent, SelectItem } from "@/shared/components/ui/select";

const form = useForm<FormData>({
  resolver: zodResolver(Schema),
  defaultValues: { firstName: "", ... }
});

<Form {...form}>
  <FormField
    control={form.control}
    name="firstName"
    render={({ field }) => (
      <FormItem>
        <FormLabel>First Name *</FormLabel>
        <FormControl>
          <Input {...field} />
        </FormControl>
        <FormMessage />
      </FormItem>
    )}
  />
</Form>
```

**Issue**: My implementation used manual `useState` instead of these shadcn form components. Want me to refactor the compensation estimator form to use the proper pattern?

